ter committing to a clean, singular outline."}	v1	0		{}	0		{}	0		{}	7	Because the figure relies almost entirely on outline, the forms remain flat; only the eye shading hints at volume. Hair, arm, and dress lack internal contour or light logic, so the drawing reads as a cut-out rather than a 3-D form.	{"Introduce simple shading: choose a light source and add broad tonal blocks on the underside of the arm, neck, and hair masses.","Use cross-contours within the hair and sleeves to wrap around the form and suggest thickness.","Study cylinder and sphere exercises, then apply their shading logic to the arm and head before adding details."}	14	The up-turned mouth, large sparkling eyes, and flowing hair transmit a cheerful, friendly vibe. The budding crown and floral accents contribute to a gentle fairy-tale atmosphere, though deeper value contrast or gesture could heighten the emotional impact.	{"Accentuate the tilt of the head or shoulders to give more personality to the pose.","Deepen eye shadows and add small catchlights to make the expression pop.","Experiment with background tones or simple patterns (e.g., soft clouds or sparkles) to reinforce the whimsical mood."}	0		{}	2025-05-06	quick sketch
