an describing where light falls, so forms lack convincing roundness.	{"Identify a single light source and shade consistently—darker in recesses (under the hood, sides of the face) and lighter on planes facing the light.","Use graduated tones rather than flat rubbing: transition from dark core shadows to mid-tones to highlights.","Break complex masses (hair, cloth) into simpler volumetric chunks first, then add texture on top."}	12	The slight smirk and downward-tilted brow give the character a playful, secretive vibe, aided by the red palette. However, the emotion could be amplified with stronger value contrast and clearer body language.	{"Deepen shadows inside the hood and under the jaw to frame the face and draw the viewer’s focus to the expression.","Enhance the lip and eyebrow shapes subtly to push the mischievous feel—small curves go a long way.","Experiment with background tone or vignette to set atmosphere instead of leaving blank paper."}	0		{}	2025-05-07	quick sketch
