 the backpack with value shifts so top, side, and front read separately.","Use a light source study (sphere-cylinder-box) before shading the final piece to internalize volumes."]},"mood_and_expression":{"score":15,"rationale":"The night sky, ruined cityscape, and the character’s posture create a contemplative, melancholic mood that comes through clearly. The faceless profile lets viewers project emotions, enhancing atmosphere.","improvement_tips":["Push the contrast between warm foreground hues and cold distant city to heighten emotional separation.","Consider adding small environmental storytelling cues—glowing embers, drifting papers—to deepen mood.","Experiment with slight body language tweaks (slumped shoulders, hand placement) to refine the emotional read."]},"value_and_light":{"score":10,"rationale":"The piece uses a basic light/dark separation (bright figure vs. darker background), but internal value range is compressed; shadows and highlights are minimal, making materials appear flat.","improvement_tips":["Identify a single key light direction and render cast shadows (e.g., boots casting on rubble, shotgun shadow) to anchor forms.","Introduce mid-tones and selective highlights on hair waves, metal gun parts, and boot edges.","Check values in grayscale to ensure the figure pops while still having internal contrast."]},"detail_and_texture":{"score":14,"rationale":"Texture overlays on walls, rubble, and clothing add grit appropriate for a post-apocalyptic scene. However, some overlays feel uniform and stamped, and the hair lacks finer strand indications compared to other surfaces.","improvement_tips":["Vary texture scale and opacity so bricks, concrete, and fabric read as different materials.","Hand-draw a few key scratches, chips, or frays on focal objects (boots, backpack) to break repetition.","Introduce selective strand clusters and stray hairs to enrich the volume without over-rendering."]},"composition_and_perspective":{"score":13,"rationale":"The rooftop ledge frames the seated figure nicely, and the diagonal shotgun balances the vertical skyline. Perspective of rubble and the ledge works, but the city’s vanishing points aren’t fully coordinated, causing slight spatial tension.","improvement_tips":["Drop faint guiding lines to ensure building façades share a common horizon line.","Consider shifting the figure slightly right or cropping in to tighten negative space on the left.","Add atmospheric perspective (lighter, bluer tones) on the farthest buildings to push depth."]},"overall_realism":{"score":11,"rationale":"The artwork lands between cartoon and semi-realistic texturing; it’s coherent but not fully believable. Limited shading and minor perspective slips keep realism at a moderate level.","improvement_tips":["Blend the stylized line art with more dimensional lighting for a cohesive semi-realistic look.","Observe real reference for folds, firearms, and rubble to refine shape specificity.","Iterate grayscale value studies before color to solidify realistic depth and material separation."]}}	\N	11	The figure’s stylized build is readable, yet the knee placement, arm length, and size of the hands feel inconsistent with the torso and head. Buildings in the background generally follow a loose perspective grid but some windows and edges drift, reducing structural believability.	{"Rough-in the figure with simple boxes and cylinders first to lock knee, elbow, and hand positions before detailing.","Use a two- or three-point perspective grid for the skyline so all verticals and horizontals converge consistently.","Mirror-flip the drawing while working to catch proportional asymmetries early."}	12	Lines are clean and uniform, giving the piece clarity, but they lack weight variation, so edges read equally regardless of importance or depth. Some outlines appear slightly shaky around the rubble and hair.	{"Introduce line-weight hierarchy—thicker lines for foreground elements, thinner for background, tapering on curves.","Prac