e sketch narrative energy.","improvement_tips":["Push contrasts around the eyes and brows to heighten emotion.","Use cooler tones in shadows and warm yellows in candlelight to amplify atmosphere.","Add subtle background elements (flickering light patterns, drifting smoke) to intensify the scene."]},"value_and_light":{"score":8,"rationale":"The yellow candle flames are a start, but surrounding forms don’t reflect their glow, resulting in weak depth and contrast.","improvement_tips":["Map a clear value range: reserve pure whites for flame highlights and deepen surrounding mid-tones.","Introduce rim-light on Belle’s hair and the Beast’s fur to show light spill.","Layer graphite or charcoal beneath colored pencil to achieve darker darks without oversaturating color."]},"detail_and_texture":{"score":8,"rationale":"Hair strands and fur are suggested, yet surfaces like fabric, wood, and stone lattice blur together and lack distinct textures.","improvement_tips":["Differentiate materials: short, directional strokes for fur, smooth blended tones for skin, cross-hatch for stone.","Add a few sharp highlights on metal candleholders to signal a reflective surface.","Observe fabric folds in capes and indicate with flowing, rhythmic lines."]},"composition_and_perspective":{"score":11,"rationale":"Placing the figures on opposite sides with candles centered creates a clear focal triangle, but the lattice windows lack consistent vanishing lines, flattening depth.","improvement_tips":["Lightly sketch a horizon line and vanishing points to align the window grid and floor.","Overlap more foreground elements (e.g., table edge) to increase spatial layering.","Tilt the candles slightly toward the viewer to reinforce 3-D perspective."]},"overall_realism":{"score":9,"rationale":"The drawing successfully conveys the story moment, yet anatomical simplifications, patchy shading, and perspective issues limit believability.","improvement_tips":["Apply a value study (simple black-and-white thumbnail) before coloring to balance realism.","Use reference photos or 3-D models for accurate facial planes and lighting.","Blend colors gradually to reduce chalky texture and smooth tonal transitions."]}}	\N	10	The two figures are recognizable and generally proportionate, yet Belle’s cranium is shortened and the Beast’s neck-to-shoulder connection feels cramped, flattening the silhouettes.	{"Lightly block in head and torso masses with simple 3-D forms before detailing to check relative sizes.","Use a vertical center-line on each face to keep features aligned in perspective.","Study side-view skull anatomy to lengthen the back of Belle’s head and correctly place the ear."}	9	Confident contour strokes outline the characters, but many lines are equally heavy and scratchy, making edges busy and hard to read.	{"Vary pressure—thicker, darker lines for foreground edges; lighter, broken lines for softer or distant contours.","Erase or soften construction lines after shading so they don’t compete with finished edges.","Practice one-stroke gesture drawing to build cleaner, more deliberate marks."}	v1	8	The yellow candle flames are a start, but surrounding forms don’t reflect their glow, resulting in weak depth and contrast.	{"Map a clear value range: reserve pure whites for flame highlights and deepen surrounding mid-tones.","Introduce rim-light on Belle’s hair and the Beast’s fur to show light spill.","Layer graphite or charcoal beneath colored pencil to achieve darker darks without oversaturating color."}	8	Hair strands and fur are suggested, yet surfaces like fabric, wood, and stone lattice blur together and lack distinct textures.	{"Differentiate materials: short, directional strokes for fur, smooth blended tones for skin, cross-hatch for stone.","Add a few sharp highlights on metal candleholders to signal a reflective surface.","Observe fabric folds in capes and indicate with flowing, rhythmic lines."}	11	Placing the figures on opposite sides with candles centered creates a