 mood, though uneven eye alignment distracts from the intended expression.","improvement_tips":["Clarify the eye directions so both irises aim consistently to reinforce the glance.","Accentuate the contrast around the mouth (light on lower lip, dark under it) for more emotive impact.","Consider a darker or lighter background halo to frame the face and heighten atmosphere."]},"value_and_light":{"score":9,"rationale":"There is an attempt at a light source from upper left, but mid-tones are missing, causing patchy darks and washed-out lights; hair and dress share similar darks, flattening separation.","improvement_tips":["Create a full 5-step value scale on scrap paper, then ensure the drawing uses at least 4 of those steps.","Blend mid-tones smoothly with tissue or stump, reserving the darkest darks for core shadows and the garment.","Introduce subtle highlights (eraser or white pencil) on hair ridge, cheekbone, and clavicle to describe light direction."]},"detail_and_texture":{"score":10,"rationale":"Individual lip lines and a few hair strokes add interest, yet hair mass reads as a single block and skin texture is uniform, giving a slightly plastic feel.","improvement_tips":["Break the hair into distinct value groups (shadow mass, mid-tone, highlight strands) rather than many equal lines.","Suggest skin pores and soft transitions with light circular shading instead of hatch lines.","Reserve sharp edges and crisp details for focal areas (eyes, lips) and loosen elsewhere."]},"composition_and_perspective":{"score":12,"rationale":"The figure sits diagonally, creating a pleasant flow, and negative space around the head breathes; however, the shoulder foreshortening could be stronger, and the top of the head nearly touches the paper edge.","improvement_tips":["Tilt the torso more or crop tighter to enhance the diagonal dynamic.","Add a faint indication of the far shoulder to improve depth and perspective.","Leave a bit more headroom or introduce a background tone to integrate the subject with the page."]},"overall_realism":{"score":10,"rationale":"The likeness is recognizable and the pose believable, but proportion slips, uneven shading, and limited value range keep the portrait from full realism.","improvement_tips":["Focus on accurate feature placement through preliminary measuring.","Study light on basic forms (sphere, cylinder) and apply those lessons to facial planes.","Gradually build values in layers, avoiding immediate dark outlines, to let realism emerge organically."]}}	\N	11	The portrait is immediately readable and the ¾ pose is clear, yet the right eye sits higher than the left, the cranium is slightly compressed, and the neck/shoulder junction is wider than anatomy suggests.	{"Lightly map the head with a sphere-and-jaw construction before detailing to keep features aligned.","Use a center-line down the face and horizontal guide lines for eyes, nose, and mouth to check symmetry.","Compare measured distances (eye-to-eye, eye-to-chin) against reference with a pencil held at arm’s length."}	12	Confident darker strokes outline the silhouette and garment, but many interior lines (hair, neck) feel hesitant or over-sketched, reducing clarity.	{"Vary pressure: use lighter, exploratory strokes for block-in, then commit with clean, darker contours.","Soften or erase construction lines once the form is established to avoid visual clutter.","Introduce tapering lines (thick–to–thin) to suggest weight and form, especially in hair strands."}	v1	9	There is an attempt at a light source from upper left, but mid-tones are missing, causing patchy darks and washed-out lights; hair and dress share similar darks, flattening separation.	{"Create a full 5-step value scale on scrap paper, then ensure the drawing uses at least 4 of those steps.","Blend mid-tones smoothly with tissue or stump, reserving the darkest darks for core shadows and the garment.","Introduce subtle highlights (eraser or white pencil) on hair ridge, cheekbone, and clavicle to